# Walkthrough - Adecos MVP

I have successfully initialized and implemented the **Adecos MVP**, an AI-powered affiliate research application.

## 1. Specifications (Protocol 1.0)
Strictly adhering to the "No Spec, No Service" protocol, I first created the required documentation:
- **[BRD](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos mvp/docs/BRD.md)**: Business Value.
- **[PRD](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos mvp/docs/PRD.md)**: UX/Behavior (Glassmorphism, No Chat Bubble).
- **[SRS](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos mvp/docs/SRS.md)**: Architecture (FastAPI + React).

## 2. Implementation

### Backend (FastAPI + Gemini)
The backend uses **FastAPI** to serve a streaming endpoint `/api/research/stream`.
It integrates with **Google Gemini API** (defaulting to `gemini-2.0-flash-exp` with fallback/user-preference support) to generate mock affiliate program data.

**Key File**: [generator.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos mvp/backend/generator.py)
```python
# Streaming logic using generate_content_async(stream=True)
async for chunk in response:
    yield chunk.text
```

### Frontend (React + Tailwind)
The frontend is a **Vite React** app styled with **Tailwind CSS**.
- **Design**: Glassmorphism (blur effects, white transparency).
- **Logic**: No chat bubbles. Input fades out/moves, output streams directly into a [ResultsTable](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos%20mvp/frontend/src/components/ResultsTable.jsx#3-95).
- **Language**: Vietnamese.

**Key File**: [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos mvp/frontend/src/App.jsx)
render_diffs(file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/adecos mvp/frontend/src/App.jsx)

### Components
- **ChatInterface**: Minimalist input with "orb" background effects.
- **ResultsTable**: Glassmorphism table with Real-time sorting and "Save" button.

## 3. Verification Results

### Backend
- **Health Check**: `http://localhost:8000/` -> `{ "status": "ok" }`. (Verified via curl).
- **Streaming Endpoint**: `POST /api/research/stream` is active and validating JSON input.

### Frontend
- **Dev Server**: Running at `http://localhost:5173`.
- **UI**: Configured with `Merriweather` serif font and Glassmorphism utilities.

> [!NOTE]
> Browser verification was limited due to a local environment issue, but backend connectivity is confirmed.

